  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "If you're looking for an iOS calendar app that allows you to \"cross off\" or mark events as completed, **Timepage by Moleskine Studio** is a great option. It\u2019s a visually stunning calendar app that lets you swipe to mark events as done, giving you a satisfying sense of progress as you move through your day.\n\nHere\u2019s why **Timepage** stands out:\n\n1. **Swipe to Complete**: You can easily swipe on events to mark them as completed, which is a simple and intuitive way to track your progress.\n2. **Smart Weather Integration**: It shows weather forecasts alongside your events, helping you plan better.\n3. **Customizable Views**: Offers day, week, and month views with a clean, minimalist design.\n4. **Event Details**: Provides detailed event information and maps, making it easy to navigate your schedule.\n\nIf Timepage doesn\u2019t fully meet your needs, here are a few alternatives to consider:\n\n- **Fantastical**: Known for its natural language input and powerful features, it allows you to mark events as completed or move them to another time.\n- **Calendar 366**: Offers a checklist-style feature for tasks and events, making it easy to track what\u2019s done.\n- **WeekCal**: Allows you to mark events as completed with a checkmark, and it\u2019s highly customizable.\n\nEach of these apps has its own strengths, so your choice will depend on your specific preferences for design and functionality. Let me know if you'd like more details about any of these!",
